		<div class="comment-body"><p>I converted an old DeWalt for this to keep in the truck.  Don&#8217;t use a cigarette lighter plug for the end (I popped a few fuses in the process).  Alligator clips or larger ring terminals directly to the battery do the trick.  Pawn shops are a great place to find tools with dead/dying batteries and you can haggle a bit more if they don&#8217;t have the charger to go with them.</p>
</div>

