		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>Hey Jack!!  Great show as always. </p>
<p>I&#8217;d like to suggest that you add pocket screw joinery equipment to the list.   Quick and easy way to build stuff.  No gluing, no clamping.   It sounded and felt like cheating a little when I started, but when I build something now, I generally will use pocket screws to do it.   Kreg makes an awesome starter kit that will pretty much do everything.   The Kreg Jr. is $40 and the face clamp is another $20.   (You&#8217;ll really have a tough time without the face clamp).  So for around $60 and a little practice, you&#8217;ll be building stuff faster and probably stronger than you had before.    I could go on and on about how awesome this system is, but it would probably start to seem as off I was affiliated with the Kreg company.  Haha.  (I&#8217;m not, by the way)</p>
<p>Keep up the good work!!!</p>
</div>

